The paper deals with the problem of recovering a low-rank matrix from a small number of linear measurements, which is a common problem in machine learning and signal processing. The paper focuses on the theoretical properties of nuclear-norm minimization algorithms, which are widely used for low-rank matrix recovery. Therefore, cs.LG (Machine Learning) is the most likely sub-category. The paper also deals with the problem of noise-corrupted measurements, which falls under cs.IT (Information Theory). The paper also discusses the use of random linear measurements, which is a topic in cs.NA (Numerical Analysis). The paper also provides error bounds, which is a topic in cs.DS (Data Structures and Algorithms) and cs.SI (Social and Information Networks).
